cription_unit\": \"None\", \"ocr_postcorrection_system\": \"None\", \"num_tokens\": -1, \"num_chars\": -1, \"quality_report\": {\"ocr_quality_score\": -1, \"cer\": -1, \"wer\": -1, \"nb_char_substitutions\": -1, \"nb_char_deletions\": -1, \"nb_char_insertions\": -1}}}","{\"document_metadata\": {\"document_id\": \"13689000\", \"primary_dataset_name\": \"overproof-combined\", \"primary_dataset_filename\": \"data/03_curated/overproof/dataset2/rawTextAndHumanCorrectionAndOverproofCorrectionTriples/allArticles.corrected.txt\", \"primary_dataset_version\": \"v1.0\", \"primary_dataset_license\": \"Very likely public domain, but not explicitly stated in original source.\", \"primary_dataset_url\": \"https://overproof.projectcomputing.com/evaluation\", \"benchmark_dataset_name\": \"hipe-ocrepair-bench-overproof\", \"benchmark_dataset_doi\": \"https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18824299\", \"benchmark_dataset_split\": \"all\", \"document_type\": \"newspaper\", \"date\": \"1888\", \"language\": \"en\", \"publication_title\": \"The Sydney Morn aid\", \"transcription_unit_scope\": \"article\", \"segmentation_origin_article\": \"primary-dataset - legacy\", \"segmentation_origin_lines\": \"primary-dataset - legacy\", \"segmentation_origin_sentences\": \"benchmark - automatic\"}, \"ground_truth\": {\"transcription_unit\": \"SOUTH AUSTRALIA.\\nADELAIDE, MONDAY.\\nThe R.M.S. Victoria sailed for Melbourne at day¬\\nlight, and the R.M.S. Orizaba, for London, this after¬\\nnoon.\\nThe funeral of the late Mr. Justice Gwynne took place\\nto-day and was largely attended by representative men\\nof the colony.\\nOne of the banks in Adelaide has given notice to its\\ncustomers that no cheques paid in will be recognised\\nunless certified by the bank upon which they are\\ndrawn.\\nOne of the 23-ton breech-loading guns for the coast\\ndefences of this colony arrived this morning by the\\nStar of Greece, from London. It is intended for the\\nGlenelg Battery. It is an Armstrong gun, and was\\nspecially designed for South Australia.\\nDr. Haacke, formerly director of the South Aus¬\\ntralian Museum, and who was the naturalist of the\\nNew Guinea Expedition under the auspices of the\\nGeographical Society of Australasia, has been elected a\\nscientific director of the Zoological Gardens at Frank¬\\nfort-on-the-Maine.\", \"line_offsets\": [[0, 16], [17, 34], [35, 83], [84, 138], [139, 144], [145, 198], [199, 252], [253, 267], [268, 320], [321, 373], [374, 422], [423, 429], [430, 481], [482, 533], [534, 585], [586, 634], [635, 674], [675, 722], [723, 772], [773, 820], [821, 876], [877, 932], [933, 951]], \"sentence_offsets\": [[0, 16], [17, 34], [35, 144], [145, 267], [268, 429], [430, 562], [563, 602], [603, 674], [675, 951]], \"num_tokens\": 135, \"num_chars\": 951, \"quality_report\": {\"ocr_quality_score\": 0.95}}, \"ocr_hypothesis\": {\"transcription_unit\": \"SOUTH AUSTRALIA.\\nADELAIDE, MONDAY.\\nThe TLM.S. Victoria sailed for Melbourne ' at day-\\nlight, \\\"and tho R.M.S. Orizaba, for London, this after-\\nnoon.\\n, The funeral of the late Mr. Justico Gwynne took placo\\nto-day and was largely attended by representative men\\nof the colony. ' *\\nOno of tho banks in Adelaide has givon notice to its\\ncustomers that no cheques paid iu will bo recognised\\nunless certified by the bank upon which thoy are\\ndrawn. '\\n: : Ono of the 23-ton breech-loading guns for the coast\\n,dofoiiccs of this colony arrived this morning by tlio\\nStar of Greece, from London. It is intended for the\\nGlenelg Battery. It is ¡m Armstrong gun, and was\\nspecially designed for South Australia.\\nDr. Haacke, formerly director of tho South Aus-\\ntralian Museum, and who was tho naturalist of the\\nNew Guinea Rxpedition under tho auspices of the\\nGeographical Society of Australasia, has been elected a\\nscientific director of tho Zoological Gardens at Prank\\nfort-on-the-Maino.\", \"line_offsets\": [[0, 16], [17, 34], [35, 85], [86, 141], [142, 147], [148, 203], [204, 257], [258, 276], [277, 329], [330, 382], [383, 431], [432, 440], [441, 496], [497, 551], [552, 603], [604, 652], [653, 692], [693, 740], [741, 790], [791, 838], [839, 894], [895, 949], [950, 968]], \"sentence_offsets\": [[0, 16], [17, 34], [35, 147], [148, 272], [273, 438], [439, 580], [581, 620], [621, 692], [693, 968]], \"num_tokens\": 142, \"num_chars\": 968, \"quality_report\": {\"ocr_quality_score\": 0.95, \"cer\": 0.051525, \"wer\": 0.22963, \"nb_char_substitutions\": 30, \"nb_char_deletions\": 1, \"nb_char_insertions\": 18}}, \"ocr_postcorrection_output\": {\"transcription_unit\": \"None\", \"ocr_postcorrection_system\": \"None\", \"num_tokens\": -1, \"num_chars\": -1, \"quality_report\": {\"ocr_quality_score\": -1, \"cer\": -1, \"wer\": -1, \"nb_char_substitutions\": -1, \"nb_char_deletions\": -1, \"nb_char_insertions\": -1}}}","{\"document_metadata\": {\"document_id\": \"14449000\", \"primary_dataset_name\": \"overproof-combined\", \"primary_dataset_filename\": \"data/03_curated/overproof/dataset2/rawTextAndHumanCorrectionAndOverproofCorrectionTriples/allArticles.corrected.txt\", \"primary_dataset_version\": \"v1.0\", \"primary_dataset_license\": \"Very likely public domain, but not explicitly stated in original source.\", \"primary_dataset_url\": \"https://overproof.projectcomputing.com/evaluation\", \"benchmark_dataset_name\": \"hipe-ocrepair-bench-overproof\", \"benchmark_dataset_doi\": \"https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18824299\", \"benchmark_dataset_split\": \"all\", \"document_type\": \"newspaper\", \"date\": \"1902\", \"language\": \"en\", \"publication_title\": \"The Sydney Morn aid\", \"transcription_unit_scope\": \"article\", \"segmentation_origin_article\": \"primary-dataset - legacy\", \"segmentation_origin_lines\": \"primary-dataset - legacy\", \"segmentation_origin_sentences\": \"benchmark - automatic\"}, \"ground_truth\": {\"transcription_unit\": \"QUARANTINE AREAS PROCLAIMED.\\nIn the Government Gazette of yesterday the\\nfollowing areas were proclaimed 