299\", \"benchmark_dataset_split\": \"all\", \"document_type\": \"newspaper\", \"date\": \"1919\", \"language\": \"en\", \"publication_title\": \"The Sydney Morn aid\", \"transcription_unit_scope\": \"article\", \"segmentation_origin_article\": \"primary-dataset - legacy\", \"segmentation_origin_lines\": \"primary-dataset - legacy\", \"segmentation_origin_sentences\": \"benchmark - automatic\"}, \"ground_truth\": {\"transcription_unit\": \"LAW NOTICES.\\nTUESDAY, MARCH 11.\\nSUPREME COURT.\\nTerm List. — In Banco Court, St. James'-road. — At 10\\na.m. — Criminal appeal : Rex v Hargan. Special case:\\nHorsfall and ors. (exors., etc.) v the Commissioner\\nfor Stamp Duties.\\nIn Chambers. — Before Mr. Justice Harvey, in No. 2\\nEquity Court, Elizabeth-street. — At 10 a.m. — Applica¬\\ntions under War Precautions Act, 1914-1916: Ex parte\\nJohn Bridge and Co., Ltd., re Anderson, to exer¬\\ncise powers under mortgage; ex parte same, re Mis¬\\nsen, ditto; ex parte Budge, re Bonser, ditto.\\nProthonotary's Office - Before the Deputy Prothono¬\\ntary: Hemphill and ors. v Bloomfield, at 11 a.m.\\nBefore the Chief Clerk: Illingworth v Illingworth,\\nRoper v Roper, at 10 a.m. : Vardy v Vardy, Boyd\\nv Boyd, at 10.15 a.m.; Wm. Adams and Co., Ltd.,\\nv Thorne, at 10.30 a.m.; M'Laughlin v Buffrey, at\\n10.45 a.m.; Smith v Smith, at 2.15 p.m.\\nIn Divorce. - Before the Judge in Divorce, in No. 3\\nCourt. - At 10.30 a.m.: Motions, etc.\\nIn Equity. - Before his Honor the Chief Judge in\\nEquity, No. 1 Court. - At 10 a.m.: Re A. T. Hog¬\\nbin and anor. and R. P. Act, for judgment; Spec¬\\nterman v Levy, motion to continue injunction.\\nBefore the Master in Equity. - At 11 a.m.: Curotta v\\nEast, to settle minutes of decree; 11.30, Shanahan v\\nMitchell, ditto; 11.45, Pearson v Commonwealth Oil\\nCorporation, to settle minutes of order; 12 noon, re\\nT. T. T. Lawry, deceased, and Convg. Act, ditto.\\nIn Bankruptcy. — Before the Registrar. — At the Supreme\\nCourt-buildings, Elizabeth-street. — At 10 a.m. — Ap¬\\nplication, for a certificate of discharge: Re George\\nBartlett. Single meeting and public examination:\\nRe J. G. Norford, re the Assigned Estate of Lucie\\nBrown, re F. J. Sutton, re Margaret Harrison; re\\nJack Baveas, re Euphemia Lennon. Public examina¬\\ntion: Re Austin Bede Chapman. Private examina¬\\ntion under Section 30: Re Sydney Wentworth Smith,\\nre Austin Bede Chapman. To settle minutes of order:\\nRe Philip Fasook Platt, at 3.30; re Louis William\\nAdams, at 3.45 p.m. ; re Oswald Lance Morton, at\\n4 p.m. Audit of Accounts and Plans. — Before the\\nChief Clerk. — At 11 a.m. — Taxation of petitioning\\ncreditor's costs: Re J. Wainwright.\\nIn Lunacy.—At 10.30 a.m.—Before the Deputy Mas¬\\nter: Re an insane patient, summons to attend.\", \"line_offsets\": [[0, 12], [13, 31], [32, 46], [47, 100], [101, 153], [154, 205], [206, 223], [224, 274], [275, 330], [331, 383], [384, 432], [433, 483], [484, 529], [530, 581], [582, 630], [631, 681], [682, 729], [730, 777], [778, 827], [828, 867], [868, 919], [920, 957], [958, 1006], [1007, 1055], [1056, 1104], [1105, 1150], [1151, 1203], [1204, 1256], [1257, 1307], [1308, 1360], [1361, 1409], [1410, 1465], [1466, 1519], [1520, 1572], [1573, 1621], [1622, 1671], [1672, 1720], [1721, 1769], [1770, 1816], [1817, 1866], [1867, 1918], [1919, 1968], [1969, 2017], [2018, 2066], [2067, 2118], [2119, 2154], [2155, 2202], [2203, 2248]], \"sentence_offsets\": [[0, 12], [13, 31], [32, 46], [47, 57], [58, 94], [95, 139], [140, 171], [172, 186], [187, 226], [227, 236], [58, 59], [239, 374], [375, 529], [530, 605], [606, 709], [710, 756], [757, 881], [882, 928], [929, 943], [944, 957], [958, 970], [971, 1029], [1030, 1069], [1070, 1150], [1151, 1181], [1182, 1193], [1194, 1397], [1398, 1409], [1410, 1424], [1425, 1450], [1451, 1500], [1501, 1582], [1583, 1753], [1754, 1799], [1800, 1890], [1891, 2053], [2054, 2079], [58, 59], [2082, 2154], [2155, 2248]], \"num_tokens\": 349, \"num_chars\": 2248, \"qual