et - legacy\", \"segmentation_origin_sentences\": \"benchmark - automatic\"}, \"ground_truth\": {\"transcription_unit\": \"LAUNCH IN TROUBLE.\\n¬\\nTaken in Tow by Rowing Boat.\\nA large launch, in which two men were fish¬\\ning broke down off Jibbon Point, on the\\nNational Park side of Port Hacking at about\\n1.30 o'clock yesterday afternoon. They were\\nabout two miles off the shore. During the\\nafternoon their distress signals were noticed\\nat Cronulla, and the police endeavoured to\\nhave a boat sent from Sydney to rescue the\\nmen.\\nA Sydney boat was not available for the\\nrescue work, and at about 3.30 two local\\nfishermen put off from Port Hacking in a\\npulling-boat to row to the disabled launch.\\nThe sea was calm, and the fishermen were\\nable to tow the launch to Port Hacking.\\nThe occupants stated that the engine had\\nfailed and that they had signalled for assist¬\\nance when the launch commenced to drift\\naway from the shore.\", \"line_offsets\": [[0, 18], [19, 20], [21, 49], [50, 93], [94, 133], [134, 177], [178, 221], [222, 263], [264, 309], [310, 352], [353, 395], [396, 400], [401, 440], [441, 481], [482, 522], [523, 566], [567, 607], [608, 647], [648, 688], [689, 735], [736, 775], [776, 796]], \"sentence_offsets\": [[0, 18], [19, 20], [21, 49], [50, 211], [212, 252], [253, 400], [401, 566], [567, 647], [648, 796]], \"num_tokens\": 124, \"num_chars\": 796, \"quality_report\": {\"ocr_quality_score\": 0.98}}, \"ocr_hypothesis\": {\"transcription_unit\": \"LAUNCH IN TROUBLE.\\nI -.\\nTaken in Tow by Rowing Boat.\\nA large launch, in which two men were fish-\\ning broke down off Jibbon Point, on the\\nNational Park side of Port Haoklng at about\\n130 o clock yesterday afternoon They were\\nabout two miles off the shore During the\\nafternoon their distress signals were noticed\\nat Cronulla, and the rjolice endeavoured to\\nhave a boat sent from Sydney to rescue the\\nmen\\nA Sydney boat was not available for the\\nrescue work, and at about 3 30 two local\\nfishermen put off from Port Hacking In a\\npulling-boat to row to the disabled launch\\nThe sea was calm and the fishermen were\\nable to to* the launch to Port Hacking\\nThe occupants stated that the engine had\\nfailed and that they had signalled for assist-\\nance when the launch commenced to drift\\naway from the shore_\", \"line_offsets\": [[0, 18], [19, 23], [24, 52], [53, 96], [97, 136], [137, 180], [181, 222], [223, 263], [264, 309], [310, 353], [354, 396], [82, 85], [401, 440], [441, 481], [482, 522], [523, 565], [566, 605], [606, 644], [645, 685], [686, 732], [733, 772], [773, 793]], \"sentence_offsets\": [[0, 18], [19, 23], [24, 52], [53, 212], [213, 252], [253, 400], [401, 565], [566, 644], [645, 793]], \"num_tokens\": 127, \"num_chars\": 793, \"quality_report\": {\"ocr_quality_score\": 0.98, \"cer\": 0.027638, \"wer\": 0.16129, \"nb_char_substitutions\": 11, \"nb_char_deletions\": 7, \"nb_char_insertions\": 4}}, \"ocr_postcorrection_output\": {\"transcription_unit\": \"None\", \"ocr_postcorrection_system\": \"None\", \"num_tokens\": -1, \"num_chars\": -1, \"quality_report\": {\"ocr_quality_score\": -1, \"cer\": -1, \"wer\": -1, \"nb_char_substitutions\": -1, \"nb_char_deletions\": -1, \"nb_char_insertions\": -1}}}","{\"document_metadata\": {\"document_id\": \"16992000\", \"primary_dataset_name\": \"overproof-combined\", \"primary_dataset_filename\": \"data/03_curated/overproof/dataset2/rawTextAndHumanCorrectionAndOverproofCorrectionTriples/allArticles.corrected.txt\", \"primary_dataset_version\": \"v1.0\", \"primary_dataset_license\": \"Very likely public domain, but not explicitly stated in original source.\", \"primary_dataset_url\": \"https://overproof.projectcomputing.com/evaluation\", \"benchmark_dataset_name\": \"hipe-ocrepair-bench-overproof\", \"benchmark_dataset_doi\": \"https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18824299\", \"benchmark_dataset_split\": \"all\", \"document_type\": \"newspaper\", \"date\": \"1933\", \"language\": \"en\", \"publication_title\": \"The Sydney Morn aid\", \"transcription_unit_scope\": \"article\", \"segmentation_origin_article\": \"primary-dataset - legacy\", \"segmentation_origin_lines\": \"primary-dataset - legacy\", \"segmentation_origin_sentences\": \"benchmark - automatic\"}, \"ground_truth\": {\"transcription_unit\": \"NEW WORKS.\\nCity architects yesterday reported that,\\nwhilst general business still showed signs of\\nimprovement, few contracts were let during\\nthe past week. There is a considerable amount\\nof remodelling being done to shops and offices\\nwithin the city, and instructions for new cot¬\\ntages and residences in the outer suburbs,\\nespecially in the northern districts, are being\\nplaced in increasing numbers.\\nJ. Aubrey Kerr, architect, has accepted the\\ntender of R. Pennington. Annandale, for al¬\\nterations to 116-118 Clarence-street, city, and\\nis calling tenders for a new boiler-house and\\ngantry at a factory in Rushcutter Bay dis¬\\ntrict .\\nFowell and McConnell have accepted the\\ntender of Alfred Stevens, Bowral, for additional\\nclassrooms at the Tudor House School, Moss\\nVale.\\nClifford H. Finch, architect, has accepted\\nthe tender of W. Huish, Campsie, for the\\nconversion of a residence in Mona-road, Dar¬\\nlinghurst, into flats, with two garages; the\\ntender of H. J. Kershaw, Lindfield, for the\\nerection of a residence in Waimea-road,\\nRoseville; and the tender of J. Bunting, city,\\nfor painting and renovations at the Church\\nof England Home for Boys, Carlingford. He\\nis preparing plans for a grandstand and\\nwaiting-room for the Woy Woy Council.\\nG. S. Keesing has accepted the tender of\\nRobert Wall and Son for alterations to busi¬\\nness premises in George-street, city.\\nPeddle, Thorpe, and Walker have accepted\\nthe tender of V. Smellie, Hurstville, for the\\nerection of a tennis clubhouse at Rockdale for\\nthe Illawarra Suburbs Lawn Tennis Associa¬\\ntion.\\nPlans have been approved by the Manly\\nCouncil, and tenders will shortly be called\\nby Emil Sodersteen, architect, for the altera¬\\ntions at the Manly Hotel and its increase in\\nheight to nine storeys. It is estimated that\\nthe additions will cost about £30,000.\\nB. Hadley, architect, has accepted the ten¬\\nder of W. Schofield for alterations and addi¬\\ntions to business premises, 362-64 Pitt-street,\\ncity, and the tender of Bray and Holliday for\\nthe shop fronts.\\nSanction has been given for the erection\\nof a new Presbyterian Church at Corowa,\\nand tenders will shortly be invited for the\\njob.\\nThe Government has approved of £4175\\nbeing expended on the remodelling of the\\nBega District Hospital.\\nA new factory is being erected in Hender¬\\nson-road, Alexandria, by M. Bowcock, builder,\\nAshfield.\\nA Scouts' hall is being erected in Abercorn¬\\nstreet. Bexley, by A. Eden, Belmore.\\nA block of flats is being erected in Victoria-\\nstreet, Lewisham, by H. Scutts, Dulwich Hill.\\nH. and E. Sidgreaves, Ltd., have secured\\ncontracts for new shop fronts and alterations\\nto Station, House, Hurstville, for Washington\\nH. Soul, Pattinson and Co. (Morrow and Gor¬\\ndon, architects); shop fronts for J. H. Marks,\\nLeeton, New South Wales (G. W. A. Welch,\\narchitect); display counters and interior fit¬\\nments to new premises, Liverpool and Castle¬\\nreagh streets, for G. J. Coles and Co., Ltd.\\n(Harry Norris, Melbourne, and Budden and\\nMackey, Sydney, architects in association).\", \"line_offsets\": [[0, 10], [11, 51], [52, 97], [98, 140], [141, 186], [187, 233], [234, 280], [281, 323], [324, 371], [372, 401], [402, 445], [446, 489], [490, 537], [538, 583], [584, 626], [627, 634], [635, 673], [674, 722], [723, 765], [766, 771], [772, 814], [815, 855], [856, 900], [901, 945], [946, 989], [990, 1029], [1030, 1076], [1077, 1119], [1120, 1161], [1162, 1201], [1202, 1239], [1240, 1280], [1281, 1325], [1326, 1363], [1364, 1404], [1405, 1450], [1451, 1497], [1498, 1540], [1541, 1546], [1547, 1584], [1585, 1628], 