t - legacy\", \"segmentation_origin_sentences\": \"benchmark - automatic\"}, \"ground_truth\": {\"transcription_unit\": \"POLITICAL.\\n- Nathaniel Hawthorne said that one of\\nthe most terrible consequences of the war\\nwould be the contentedness of the Ameri¬\\ncan people with one bullet-headed general,\\nas president, for another, for the next\\nthirty years.\\n- Bob Toombs, of Georgia, who says\\nwhat he thinks much more boldly than Jeff\\nDavis, is to be called before the Congres¬\\nsional anti-ku-klux committee to give his\\ntestimony as to the condition of the south.\\nWe hope Toombs will respond, for he may\\nbe enable to let us know what is his\\nground for the faith that is in him that\\nthe southern people want another war.\\nHe talked war enough to revolutionize the\\nwestern hemisphere to our correspondent\\nrecently, and we are curious to see what\\nhe will say to the congressional committee\\non that head. - New-York Herald.\\nHon. Ben. H. Hill's presence at the\\ndinner given by Gov. Bullock to senator\\nCameron and other northern republicans, a\\nfew nights since, at Atlanta, has furnished\\nthe Macon (Ga.) Telegraph and Messenger\\na startling verification that times change\\nand men change with them, and it says:\\n\\\"Perhaps the gulf that now intervenes be¬\\ntween the people of this land and that\\npeace and accord so much needed, might\\nnot now be so deep and wide had fewer\\nbitter words been spoken on both sides.'\", \"line_offsets\": [[0, 10], [11, 49], [50, 91], [92, 132], [133, 175], [176, 215], [216, 229], [230, 264], [265, 306], [307, 349], [350, 391], [392, 435], [436, 475], [476, 512], [513, 553], [554, 591], [592, 633], [634, 673], [674, 714], [715, 757], [758, 790], [791, 826], [827, 866], [867, 908], [909, 952], [953, 992], [993, 1035], [1036, 1074], [1075, 1116], [1117, 1155], [1156, 1194], [1195, 1232], [1233, 1273]], \"sentence_offsets\": [[0, 10], [11, 229], [230, 435], [436, 591], [592, 771], [772, 790], [791, 1273]], \"num_to