r times Mrs.\\nJenkins and her family narrowly escaped en¬\\ncounters with bushrangers. Her memory and\\nsight are exceptionally good. She reads with¬\\nout the aid of glasses, and often goes for the\\nmails. For many years she has never missed\\nexercising the franchise, and her comments\\non present-day affairs are keen and to the\\npoint.\u0026quot;, \u0026quot;line_offsets\u0026quot;: [[0, 14], [15, 29], [30, 49], [50, 90], [91, 135], [136, 182], [183, 190], [191, 209], [210, 251], [252, 295], [296, 341], [342, 387], [388, 433], [434, 450], [451, 492], [493, 539], [540, 582], [583, 626], [627, 674], [675, 719], [720, 761], [762, 801], [802, 847], [848, 893], [894, 939], [940, 986], [987, 1029], [1030, 1071], [1072, 1115], [1116, 1157], [1158, 1203], [1204, 1250], [1251, 1293], [1294, 1336], [1337, 1379], [1380, 1386]], \u0026quot;sentence_offsets\u0026quot;: [[0, 14], [15, 29], [30, 49], [50, 190], [191, 195], [196, 209], [210, 450], [451, 547], [548, 661], [662, 768], [769, 854], [855, 902], [903, 1051], [1052, 1142], [1143, 1187], [1188, 1257], [1258, 1386]], \u0026quot;num_tokens\u0026quot;: 205, \u0026quot;num_chars\u0026quot;: 1386, \u0026quot;quality_report\u0026quot;: {\u0026quot;ocr_quality_score\u0026quot;: 0.94}}, \u0026quot;ocr_hypothesis\u0026quot;: {\u0026quot;transcription_unit\u0026quot;: \u0026quot;A CENTENARIAN.\\nActive at 101.\\nAN EPPING RESIDENT.\\nProbably the oldest living woman in Aus-\\ntralia Is Mrs. John Jenkins, now living with\\nher daughters, Mrs. Beveridge, at Blairgowrie,\\nEpping.\\nMRS. JOHN JENKINS.\\nMrs. Jenkins IB in her 102nd year, having\\nbeen born near Campbelltown on May l8,1822,\\nShe haB thus lived through the reigns of four\\nor five rulers of Great Britain, and has seen\\nSydney develop from a village on the banks of\\n| the Tank Stream.\\nIn splto of the weight of 102 years, Mrs.\\nJenkins still enjoys good health, and is still\\nactive. At her home may be seen four gene-\\nrations together-mother, daughter, grand-