overnment\nfor more than £20,000. He\nsaid that of the 31 people who\nhad been allotted homes on the\nestate without ballot 11 were\nPublic servants.]\nWhile Kuring-gai Council\nwas discussing the Water\nBoard&#39;s letter Alderman E.\nSolomon said other areas in\nthe municipality had been\ndeveloped for years without\nany hint of their being\nsewered.\n\&quot;We now find the Archbold\nEstate is getting preference\nover all other areas in the dis¬\ntrict which have waited for\nyears for sewerage,\&quot; he said.\nAlderman A. Campbell,\nrepresentative for the Water\nBoard, said: \&quot;This is called a\nshort extension and it is not\na priority. It is the policy of\nthe Water Board to do short\nextensions. The Housing Com¬\nmission doesn&#39;t get priorities.\&quot;\nAld. Solomon: Some people\nhave waited 15 years for the\nsewer.\nAld. Campbell: The Housing\nCommission is not getting a\npriority.\nAlter the meeting Alderman\nSolomon said: \&quot;There is no\ndoubt that pressure has been\nbrought to bear on the Water\nBoard. I think the Minister,\nor if not the Minister then\nthe Housing Commission, has\nused some pressure. There\nare only five or six houses\nalready built on the estate and\nonly 26 to be built.\&quot;&quot;, &quot;line_offsets&quot;: [[0, 22], [23, 45], [46, 65], [66, 86], [87, 111], [112, 130], [131, 157], [158, 190], [191, 216], [217, 231], [232, 257], [258, 288], [289, 318], [319, 347], [348, 370], [371, 378], [379, 407], [408, 436], [437, 466], [467, 495], [496, 526], [527, 552], [553, 583], [584, 614], [615, 644], [645, 662], [663, 687], [688, 712], [713, 739], [740, 767], [768, 793], [794, 821], [822, 845], [846, 854], [855, 880], [881, 909], [910, 942], [943, 970], [971, 1000], [1001, 1022], [1023, 1051], [1052, 1082], [1083, 1112], [1113, 1144], [1145, 1172], [1173, 1201], [1202, 1234], [1235, 1260], [1261, 1289], [1290, 1296], [1297, 1323], [1324, 1351], [1115, 1124], [1362, 1388], [1389, 1415], [1416, 1444], [1445, 1473], [1474, 1502], [150