e to let us know what is his\nground for the faith that is in him that\nthe southern people want another war.\nHe talked war enough to revolutionize the\nwestern hemisphere to our correspondent\nrecently, and we are curious to see what\nhe will say to the congressional committee\non that head. - New-York Herald.\nHon. Ben. H. Hill&#39;s presence at the\ndinner given by Gov. Bullock to senator\nCameron and other northern republicans, a\nfew nights since, at Atlanta, has furnished\nthe Macon (Ga.) Telegraph and Messenger\na startling verification that times change\nand men change with them, and it says:\n\&quot;Perhaps the gulf that now intervenes be¬\ntween the people of this land and that\npeace and accord so much needed, might\nnot now be so deep and wide had fewer\nbitter words been spoken on both sides.&#39;&quot;, &quot;line_offsets&quot;: [[0, 10], [11, 49], [50, 91], [92, 132], [133, 175], [176, 215], [216, 229], [230, 264], [265, 306], [307, 349], [350, 391], [392, 435], [436, 475], [476, 512], [513, 553], [554, 591], [592, 633], [634, 673], [674, 714], [715, 757], [758, 790], [791, 826], [827, 866], [867, 908], [909, 952], [953, 992], [993, 1035], [1036, 1074], [1075, 1116], [1117, 1155], [1156, 1194], [1195, 1232], [1233, 1273]], &quot;sentence_offsets&quot;: [[0, 10], [11, 229], [230, 435], [436, 591], [592, 771], [772, 790], [791, 1273]], &quot;num_tokens&quot;: 192, &quot;num_chars&quot;: 1273, &quot;quality_report&quot;: {&quot;ocr_quality_score&quot;: 0.97}}, &quot;ocr_hypothesis&quot;: {&quot;transcription_unit&quot;: &quot;POLITICAL.\nNalhnniol Hawthorne said thatono of\ntho most tcrriblo consequences of the wur\nwould bo tho contcntcdncss of tho Ameri\ncan people with one bullet-headed general,\nas prcsid.&#39;int, nftor another, for .the next\nthirty years.\nHob Toombs, of (Jeorgin, who says\nwhat he thinks much more boldly than .letl\&quot;\nJ).ivis, is to bu called beloro tho Congres\nsional uuti-ku-klux&#39; coinmittco to give his\ntestimony as 