<div id="LC26" class="react-code-text react-code-line-contents-no-virtualization react-file-line html-div ">{&quot;document_metadata&quot;: {&quot;document_id&quot;: &quot;sn88074142-10-00280761485-1872040501-1138&quot;, &quot;primary_dataset_name&quot;: &quot;overproof-combined&quot;, &quot;primary_dataset_filename&quot;: &quot;data/03_curated/overproof/dataset3/rawTextAndHumanCorrectionAndOverproofCorrectionTriples/allArticles.corrected.txt&quot;, &quot;primary_dataset_version&quot;: &quot;v1.0&quot;, &quot;primary_dataset_license&quot;: &quot;Very likely public domain, but not explicitly stated in original source.&quot;, &quot;primary_dataset_url&quot;: &quot;https://overproof.projectcomputing.com/evaluation&quot;, &quot;benchmark_dataset_name&quot;: &quot;hipe-ocrepair-bench-overproof&quot;, &quot;benchmark_dataset_doi&quot;: &quot;https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18824299&quot;, &quot;benchmark_dataset_split&quot;: &quot;all&quot;, &quot;document_type&quot;: &quot;newspaper&quot;, &quot;date&quot;: &quot;1872&quot;, &quot;language&quot;: &quot;en&quot;, &quot;publication_title&quot;: &quot;THE CARIRO DAILY (ILLINOIS)&quot;, &quot;transcription_unit_scope&quot;: &quot;article&quot;, &quot;segmentation_origin_article&quot;: &quot;primary-dataset - legacy&quot;, &quot;segmentation_origin_lines&quot;: &quot;primary-dataset - legacy&quot;, &quot;segmentation_origin_sentences&quot;: &quot;benchmark - automatic&quot;}, &quot;ground_truth&quot;: {&quot;transcription_unit&quot;: &quot;HINTS OF FASHION.\n- Linen suits are principally cut with a\nskirt and polonaise, the latter generally\nthe Marguerite.\n- All the new over-skirts are made\nlong - very long at the back, but draped\nhigh at the sides, with the apron front.\n- On black satin striped grenadine bias\nruffles may be used as trimmings; on\nstriped organdy bias ruffles or bias bands,\nedged with lace.\n- New tinted scarfs for street wear are\ncomposed of twilled silk, with wide dia¬\ngonal stripes, shaded from dark to light in\nthe same color.\n- Fine embroidery wrought in the\nlinen is now the fashionable method of or¬\nnamenting underclothing, and is much\nmore suitable as well as more durable\nthan lace or ruffling.\n- Neck ties or bows are of pale twilled\nsilk, with or without fringed ends, the\nfringe forming knotted tassels. Others\nare of twilled silk edged with Valen¬\nciennes, the ends forming a cascade com¬\nposed of alternate shades of silk and lace.\n- As the warm weather advances many\ndifferent styles for suits will be introduced,\nbut the skirt and the polonaise will be\nmainly adhered to, and the simpler the\ndesign for washing materials the better it\nlooks, and the longer it retains its fresh\nappearance.\n- Satin striped organdy is a novelty in\nwhite muslin; the stripes are an inch\nbroad and have a satin finished surface.\nIt \&quot;does up\&quot; nicely and will make pretty\nsummer suits or house dresses, and it will\nneed but little trimming. Black satin-\nstriped grenadine is used this season in¬\nstead of the black with a white stripe,\nwhich was so much in vogue last year.\nOf course both will be worn, but the all\nblack is later and considered more lady¬\nlike. GLEANINGS.\n- It is reported that there are seventy-\nfive counties in Texas in which there is\nnot a single Sunday school.\n- Widow Fay of Oregon has set up a\ncigar manufactory, and her weeds are said\nto be the best in the state.\n- Converted Indians sing \&quot;Now I Lay\nMe\&quot; with warwhoop accompaniment.\nThe effect is said to be very soothing.\n- The Japanese make a strong string of\npaper, and we have seen a very good cord\nof wood, but not lately. - [Boston Trans.\n- A correspondent from Salt Lake City\nsays the Mormon girls have the freshest\nfairest, clearest, and most healthy comp¬\nlexions he ever saw.\n- Within the last ten years 160,000,000\nacres of public lands have been given away,\nnot, however, to the landless, homeless,\nthe hymonial platform, adjusted the fatal\nnoose, and swung off into that unsilent\nbourne whence he can never return, save\nby the Indianapolis connecting lines.\&quot;\n- An embryo Barnum of nine years, in\nVirginia City, Nevada, painted his little,\nbrother in the latest style of the fierce\nSioux, and exhibited him as a captured\nson of Spotted Tail, at twenty-five cents a\nticket. His mother attended the show\nand recognised and claimed her darling\nson.\n- For several months past W. H. Allen,\nM. D., has been living in Bloomington,\nhealing the blind and afflicted, occupying\nrooms in the People&#39;s bank block. He\ncame to a climax on Tuesday night by\neloping with the wife of a German named\nBomgardner, who lives somewhere near\nthe \&quot;Forty Acres.\&quot;\n- The scientific men who have been\nwatching Mount Vesuvius for the past\nmonth declare that there are unmistaka¬\nble indications that a spout will occur\nwithin another month. The mountain is\ngroaning and sighing, clouds of ashes are\nbeing blown out, and a warning has been\ngiven near inhabitants to gather their\nhousehold effects and remove to safer\nplaces.\n- A good story is told of a St. Louis\nnobby dry goods clerk who attended a\ndance in the rural district a few eve¬\nnings since. He wore a Cheviot shirt, and\nput on a great many airs. He was some¬\nwhat taken down, however, when he over¬\nheard one country lass say to another:\n\&quot;That St Louis chap slings on a heap of\nstyle for a feller that wears a bed-tick\nshirt.\&quot;&quot;, &quot;line_offsets&quot;: [[0, 17], [18, 58], [59, 100], [101, 116], [117, 151], [152, 192], [193, 233], [234, 273], [274, 310], [311, 354], [355, 371], [372, 411], [412, 452], [453, 496], [497, 512], [513, 545], [546, 588], [589, 625], [626, 663], [664, 686], [687, 726], [727, 766], [767, 805], [806, 843], [844, 884], [885, 928], [929, 964], [965, 1011], [1012, 1051], [1052, 1090], [1091, 1133], [1134, 1176], [1177, 1188], [1189, 1228], [1229, 1266], [1267, 1307], [1308, 1348], [1349, 1391], [1392, 14