 said at\na Fourth of July celebration, \&quot;Gen¬\ntlemen, let us not forget that we\nwere all Englishmen until we signed\nthe Declaration of Independence.\&quot;\nAnd on another occasion, when the\nevacuation of Yorktown was men¬\ntioned in a half apologetic way by a\nspeaker at a banquet where a com¬\npany of English gentlemen were\npresent, I heard him in his pleasant,\nhumorous way remark, \&quot;Anybody\nwho knows Yorktown couldn&#39;t be\nsurprised at the English general\nbeing quite willing to get out.\&quot;\nWith a native American&#39;s love for\nhis country Gen. Porter has a hearty\nadmiration for this other land of\nliberty which has set the example of\nfreedom to the whole world. - Joseph\nHatton in Cigarette Papers.&quot;, &quot;line_offsets&quot;: [[0, 29], [30, 61], [62, 98], [99, 131], [132, 164], [165, 197], [198, 230], [231, 262], [263, 297], [298, 334], [335, 369], [370, 403], [404, 441], [442, 476], [477, 512], [513, 546], [547, 582], [583, 616], [617, 650], [651, 682], [683, 719], [720, 753], [754, 784], [785, 822], [823, 852], [853, 883], [884, 916], [917, 949], [950, 983], [984, 1020], [1021, 1054], [1055, 1091], [1092, 1128], [1129, 1156]], &quot;sentence_offsets&quot;: [[0, 29], [30, 256], [257, 342], [343, 454], [455, 616], [617, 949], [950, 1119], [1120, 1156]], &quot;num_tokens&quot;: 171, &quot;num_chars&quot;: 1156, &quot;quality_report&quot;: {&quot;ocr_quality_score&quot;: 0.91}}, &quot;ocr_hypothesis&quot;: {&quot;transcription_unit&quot;: &quot;The New Ambassador to Franco\nGen Horace Porter the new Am\nbassador to France is thn author of\ntho most comploto and comprehen\nsive history of Grants military\ncareer now appearing iu Th Cen\ntury Magazino undor tho title of\nCampaigning with Grant Wash\nington is very hapjr in her repre\nsentative at the principal courts of\nEurope Gen Portor a worthy suc\ncessor of Mr Whitolaw Rsid is a\nrnan of wit a scholar a oolclior and\na gentleman It was ho who said at\na Fourth of July celebration Gen\ntlemen let us uot forget that wo\nwere all Englishmen until we signed\ntho Declaration of Indopendonoo\nAnd on another occasion when the\nevacuation of Yorktown was men\ntioned iu a half apologntio way by a\nspeaker at a banquet where a com\npany of English gentlemen were\npresent I heard him in his pleasant\nhumorous way remark Anybody\nwho kuows Yorktown couldnt be\nsurprised at the English general\nbaing quite willing to get out\nWith a nativo Americans love for\nhis country Gun Portor has a hearty\nadmiration for this other land of\nliberty which -has set tho exampla of\nfreedom to the whole world Joieph\nIlailon in Cigarette Papers&quot;, &quot;line_offsets&quot;: [[0, 28], [29, 57], [58, 93], [94, 125], [126, 157], [158, 188], [189, 221], [222, 249], [250, 283], [284, 320], [321, 351], [352, 383], [384, 420], [421, 454], [455, 487], [488, 520], [521, 556], [557, 588], [589, 621], [622, 652], [653, 689], [690, 722], [723, 753], [754, 789], [790, 817], [818, 847], [848, 880], [881, 911], [912, 944], [945, 980], [981, 1014], [1015, 1052], [1053, 1086], [1087, 1114]], &quot;sentence_offsets&quot;: [[0, 28], [29, 244], [245, 327], [328, 432], [433, 588], [589, 911], [912, 1079], [1080, 1115]], &quot;num_tokens&quot;: 170, &quot;num_chars&quot;: 1114, &quot;quality_report&quot;: {&quot;ocr_quality_score&quot;: 0.87, &quot;cer&quot;: 0.077855, &quot;wer&quot;: 0.368421, &quot;nb_char_substitutions&quot;: 40, &quot;nb_char_deletions&quot;: 46, &quot;nb_char_insertions&quot;: 4}}, &quot;ocr_postcorrection_output&quot;: {&quot;transcription_unit&quot;: &quot;None&quot;, &quot;ocr_postcorrection_system&quot;: &quot;None&quot;, &quot;num_tokens&quot;: -1, &quot;num_chars&quot;: -1, &quot;quality_report&quot;: {&quot;ocr_quality_score&quot;: -1, &quot;cer&quot;: -1, &quot;wer&quot;: -1, &quot;nb_char_substitutions&quot;: -1, &quot;nb_char_deletions&quot;: -1, &quot;nb_char_insertions&quot;: -1}}}</div>
<div id="LC29" class="react-code-text react-code-line-contents-no-virtualization react-file-line html-div ">{&quot;document_metadata&quot;: {&quot;document_id&quot;: &quot;sn85066387-4-noissue-190003011-0003&quot;, &quot;primary_dataset_name&quot;: &quot;overproof-combined&quot;, &quot;primary_dataset_filename&quot;: &quot;data/03_curated/overproof/dataset3/rawTextAndHumanCorrectionAndOverproofCorrectionTriples/allArticles.corrected.txt&quot;, &quot;primary_dataset_version&quot;: &quot;v1.0&quot;, &quot;primary_dataset_license&quot;: &quot;Very likely public domain, but not explicitly stated in original source.&quot;, &quot;primary_dataset_url&quot;: &quot;https://overproof.projectcomputing.com/evaluation&quot;, &quot;benchmark_dataset_name&quot;: &quot;hipe-ocrepair-bench-overproof&quot;, &quot;benchmark_dataset_doi&quot;: &quot;https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18824299&quot;, &quot;benchmark_dataset_split&quot;: &quot;all&quot;, &quot;document_type&quot;: &quot;newspaper&quot;, &quot;date&quot;: &quot;1900&quot;, &quot;language&quot;: &quot;en&quot;, &quot;publication_title&quot;: &quot;THE SAN FRANCISCO CALL&quot;, &quot;transcription_unit_scope&quot;: &quot;article&quot;, &quot;segmentation_origin_article&quot;: &quot;primary-dataset - legacy&quot;, &quot;segmentation_origin_lines&quot;: &quot;primary-dataset - legacy&quot;, &quot;segmentation_origin_sentences&quot;: &quot;benchmark - automatic&quot;}, &quot;ground_truth&quot;: {&quot;transcription_unit&quot;: &quot;ROBERTS GRATEFUL\nFOR QUEEN&#39;S WORDS\nLONDON, Feb. 28. - In her dispatch to\nLord Roberts following the announcement\nof the surrender of General Cronje her\nMajesty said:\n\&quot;Accept for yourself and all under your\ncommand my warmest congratulations on\nthis splendid news.\&quot;\nLord Roberts replied as follows:\n\&quot;All under my command are deeply\ngrateful for your Majesty&#39;s most gracious\nmessage. Congratulations from their\nQueen are an honor the soldiers dearly\nprize.\&quot;\nGeneral Buller has wired his thanks to\nthe Queen for her telegram of gracious\nsympathy and encouragement.\nCONGRESSMEN TO CRONJE.\nWASHINGTON, Feb. 28.— Representa¬\ntive Fitzgerald of Massachusetts to-day\npassed around among his Democratic col¬\nleagues the following cable to General\nCronje, the defeated Boer general. Up to\nto-day, about thirty of them had signed it:\n\&quot;General Cronje, Cape Town, Africa:\nMembers of the United States House of\nRepresentatives congratulate you and\nyour soldiers on the magnificent display\nof courage and heroism in your brave\nfight for human rights.\&quot;\nCONFLICTS AT BELFAST.\nBELFAST, Feb. 28. - A rumor, that\nLadysmith had been relieved led to street\ndemonstrations in Belfast to-day which\nprecipitated conflicts between the Orange¬\nmen and Nationalists. There was consid¬\nerable stone throwing and many persons\nwere injured and some property damaged.\nBOERS SAID TO USE\nEXPLOSIVE BULLETS\nROBERTS IMPRESSED\nBY CRONJE&#39;S INGENUITY\nLONDON, March 1. - Winston Churchill,\nin a dispatch from Colenso dated Tuesday,\nsays:\n\&quot;The condition of the wounded who were\nuntended on the hillside Sunday was so\npainful that General Buller sent a flag of\ntruce to the enemy and it was arranged\nthat throughout Sunday military move¬\nments should continue on both sides, but\nthere should be no shooting. This truce\nterminated at dusk. The Boers then re¬\nsumed a furious musketry attack on the\nBritish left. The attack was repulsed.\nFighting continues vigorously. We shall\nsee who can stand &#39;bucketing&#39; best, the\nBriton or the Boer.\&quot;\nMr. Churchill goes on to say that there\nis abundant proof of the Boers using a\nlarger proportion of illegal bullets, no\nfewer than five different kinds of explod¬\ning or expanding bullets having been\nfound. He also asserts that the Boers are\nemploying armed Kaffirs, and he adds:\n\&quot;I have always tried to be fair toward\nthe Boers, but after making every allow¬\nance it must be said that they show when\nin stress a very dark, cruel and vengeful\nunderside of character.\&quot;\nFOOD IS YET SCARCE.\nKIMBERLEY, Feb. 28. - Colonel Peak¬\nman, with a mounted force and a Maxim,\nproceeded to Barkley West, where he was\nwarmly welcomed. He left a strong guard,\nand then proceeded to Longlands. Wind¬\nsortown and Klopdam. There were ru¬\nmors of Boers in the neighborhood, but no\ndemonstration occurred.\nThe Diamondfield Advertiser draws\npointed attention to the fact that al¬\nthough Kimberley was relieved about two\nweeks ago, there has been no amelioration\nin regard to the food supply. It is still\nimpossible, as it was during the invest¬\nment, to procure a tin of condensed milk\nor cocoa without a medical certificate.\nThe inhabitants continue without many\nof the common articles of food, although\nmeat rations have been increased to half\na pound.&quot;, &quot;line_offsets&quot;: [[0, 16], [17, 34], [35, 72], [73, 112], [113, 151], [152, 165], [166, 205], [206, 243], [244, 264], [265, 297], [298, 330], [331, 372], [373, 408], [409, 447], [448, 455], [456, 494], [495, 533], [534, 561], [562, 584], [585, 618], [619, 658], [659, 698], [699, 737], [738, 778], [779, 822], [823, 858], [859, 896], [897, 933], [934, 974], [975, 1011], [1012, 1036], [1037, 1058], [1059, 1092], [1093, 1134], [1135, 1173], [1174, 1216], [1217, 1256], [1257, 1295], [1296, 1335], [1336, 1353], [1354, 1371], [1372, 1389], [1390, 1411], [1412, 1449], [1450, 1491], [1492, 1497], [1498, 1536], [1537, 1575], [1576, 1618], [1619, 1657], [1658, 1695], [1696, 1736], [1737, 1776], [1777, 1815], [1816, 1854], [1855, 1893], [1894, 1933], [1934, 1973], [1974, 1994], [1995, 2034], [2035, 2073], [2074, 2114], [2115, 2157], [2158, 2194], [2195, 2236], [2237, 2274], [2275, 2313], [2314, 2354], [2355, 2395], [2396, 2437], [2438, 2462], [2463, 2482], [2483, 2518], [2519, 2557], [2558, 2597], [2598, 2638], [2639, 2677], [2678, 2713], [2714, 2755], [2756, 2779], [2780, 2813], [2814, 